Website - Bhuvan IMD Weather Products (Indian Meteorological Department)
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app1.nrsc.gov.in/imd/
Website Content Details -
Bhuvan is a web-based geoportal developed by the National Remote Sensing Centre (NRSC) of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). It provides access to a wide range of Indian Earth Observation (EO) data products and services, including weather data from the India Meteorological Department (IMD).

The IMD weather products available on Bhuvan include:

Surface Weather data, such as temperature, humidity, wind speed, cloud cover, and rainfall.
Satellite Weather data, such as cloud cover, precipitation, and sea surface temperature.
Radar Weather data, such as rainfall intensity and location.
These data products can be used to visualize and analyze weather patterns and conditions across India. They are useful for a variety of purposes, including:

Weather forecasting
Disaster management
Agriculture
Transportation
Public health
To access IMD weather products on Bhuvan, you can select the "IMD" layer from the "Layers" menu. You can then select the specific data product you want to view.

For example, to view the current surface weather conditions in Hyderabad, you would select the "Surface Weather" layer, and then zoom in to Hyderabad. The map will display the current temperature, humidity, wind speed, cloud cover, and rainfall in Hyderabad.

You can also use Bhuvan to view historical weather data. To do this, you can select the "Time" option from the "Layers" menu. You can then select the start and end dates for the data you want to view.

Bhuvan is a valuable resource for anyone who wants to learn more about the weather in India. It provides a wealth of data and tools that can be used to visualize and analyze weather patterns and conditions.

 
